hr  at dell home wins our vote it has almost all of the same features as the charge   at dell home our old favorite tracker but in a design that is  percent slimmer with better battery life the alta hr has continuous heartrate basic phone notifications and after wearing it for weeks its proven to be a great fitness  at amazoncom companionfor me its all about design ive been wearing the alta hr for almost a month and plan to continue wearing it even after this review its comfortable to wear and doesnt sacrifice any features but what sold me was the seven day battery life now if only it were swimproof like the flex   at dell home then it would have been a grand slam the alta hr costs  £ or au the same price as the charge  for most people the charge s extra few features probably arent worth it if you do care about manually tracking workouts or having a stopwatch get the charge  otherwise the alta hr is the fitness tracker we recommend a slim heart rate trackerfitbits heart rate tracking has finally found its way into a smaller band the alta hr is the same size as the original alta  at dell home and has all of the same features plus heart rate it can track steps distance calories burned active minutes and sleep to look at these stats just tap the alta hrs case below the screen the display isnt touchsensitive but the alta hr can detect forceful taps unfortunately it doesnt do stair climbing or have a relax mode like the charge  the alta hr top compared to the original alta bottom sarah tewcnet the trackers narrow monochrome led will also display notifications for incoming calls text messages and calendar alerts and will provide reminders to move throughout the day as i said with the original alta though these notifications can be difficult to read due to the small display the heart rate sensor measures heart rate at second intervals continuously throughout the day this is the same as the charge  and blaze  at dell home but both of those can also manually start workouts which increase the sample rate to once every second in everyday use over a few weeks i didnt miss that faster heart rate sampling but serious workout warriors might sarah tewcnet the fitbit app provides a graph of allday heart rate and resting heart rate it also displays a personalized cardio fitness score this is the same score that debuted last fall on the charge  and is slated to arrive on the blaze its an estimate of overall health that is based on your vo max a widely accepted metric that is used to determine how well our bodies can use oxygen during workouts a stylish tracker with long battery lifethe alta hr supports a wide variety of swappable bands there are rubber ones in multiple colors and even more stylish leather and metal options the straps from the original alta will work with the alta hr and vice versa swappable bands also mean less wear and tear on the actual fitbit device sarah tewcnet while the straps are backward compatible the clipon proprietary charging cable isnt luckily you wont have to charge it often the alta hr will last an entire week on a single charge which is damn impressive given the small size best wearable tech of  see all fitbit charge  starting at  just about everything you need for fitness except gps and water resistance apple watch series  starting at  gps waterproofing and faster software make apples new smartwatch finally click but garmin vivomove starting at  its a stylish analog watch with long battery life and fitness tracking garmin forerunner  starting at  the forerunner  tracks pace and distance provides easytoread smartphone alerts and huawei watch starting at  the huawei watch features the highest resolution display of any android wear watch and dan graziano dan graziano is an associate editor for cnet his work has appeared on bgr fox news fox business and yahoo news among other publications when he isnt tinkering with the latest gadgets and gizmos he can be found enjoying the sights and sounds of new york city see ful