oftware is available heretalent management software overviewwhat is talent managementtalent management is sometimes considered a synonym for performance management however in reality talent management software is a set of hr capabilities—including but not limited to performance management—that are considered strategically important to the organization one possible definition is that talent management software is designed to manage talent through the entire lifecycle from talent acquisition through development to reward and measurement in order to ensure that the best people are being hired developed and trained and compensated to maximize value for the organizationtalent management solutionsthe primary constituent elements of talent management suites form a continuum of activities and processes revolving around the most important resource in any organizationits people the primordial talent concerns of most organizations includetalent acquisition especially improving the quality of hiresspeeding up the time to competencyimproving performance and developmentmaking sure that everyone is working on projects with the highest potential for impactensuring that talent is rewarded and compensatedfinding a new generation of leaderscontinuously developing staff to meet the fast changing needs of the modern corporationa talent management system is designed specifically to help organizations solve common hr pain points and meet these highly strategic goalstalent management software features  capabilitiesthe various talent management components are as follows recruitmentats recruiting or talent acquisition is considered a key component of talent management these features may be delivered as a module within a talent management suite or through integration with a standalone recruitingats tool typical recruitment features includejob requisition managementcompany website postingsocial media publishingjob search site postingcustomizable application formsresume managementduplicate candidate preventioncandidate searchapplicant trackingcollaborationtask creation and delegationemail templates for communication with candidatesuser permissionsnotifications and alerts particularly for interviewsstandard reports on key recruiting metrics such as timetofillonboardingemployee onboarding is the process or orienting new hires to the social and performance aspects of their jobs so that they are able to function in their new roles as quickly as possible talent management features to help with onboarding often includenew hire portalmanager tracking toolscompliance tracking and reportingperformance management  compensation managementperformance management is the process of ensuring employees meet predetermined objectives and goals through regular checkins and appraisals compensation management involves determining employee pay grades salary bonuses commission etc based on performance metrics features around performance and compensation management areperformance plans and performance improvement plansplan weighingmanager note takingreview status tracking review reminders and review transfermultiple review frequencyrater nominations and rater nomination workflowworkflow restrictionsreportinggoal alignmenttalent management solutions often have features that help to measure and improve performance in relation to specific business goals goal alignment is the practice of ensuring that all employees have clearly defined goals in support of the overall corporate strategy the term cascading goal alignment refers to the synchronization of goals at different levels these features support goal alignmentcorporate subordinate and individual goal settingnonhierarchal goal settinglineofsightvisibilityperformance trackingsuccession planning  learning managementsuccession planning is the identification and development of internal employees with the potential to fill key business leadership positions in the company learning management is the process of planning and assisting with employee training in new skills often to prepare employees for new andor higher level positions standalone learning management systems are available internal succession is often dependent on successful learning management features in this area allow users tocreate succession planspoolsrank candidatesmanage and update employee profilessearch for candidatesadd new candidatesassign learning and development goals to candidatestalent management listings listings   all types   listingssearchlistings  of sort by reviews  highest rated  lowest rated  alphabetical  product  service ultiproultimate software delivers cloudbased hcm solutions that help businesses accelerate talent acquisition simplify payroll computations manage time and attendance and support proactive strategic talent managementreviews alternativesultipro product tour adp workforce nowadp workforce now is an cloudbased hr platform for midsized businessesreviews alternativescompare adp workforce now oracle hcm cloudoracle hcm aims to go beyond the basics of hr according to the vendor an attractive ui social mobile and reporting capabilities are now table stakes of every hr solution oracle hcm aims to allow its users to become strategic leaders of talent by being engaging informative andreviews alternativesvisit website cornerstone ondemandcornerstone ondemand is a cloudbased application for talent management the companys solutions help businesses recruit train manage and engage their employeesreviews alternativescompare cornerstone ondemand workday human capital managementworkday human capital management offers intuitive selfservice features to help effectively organize staff and pay a global workforce automating the hiretoretire lifecycle for all an organizations personnel under one cloudbased umbrella workday hcm is a comprehensive offering toutingreviews alternativescompare workday human capital management icims talent acquisition software suiteicims is an applicant tracking software for companies of all s